<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-143-612  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 143 612.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Database Systems  March 1989 v14 n1 p1(27).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>On the translation of relational queries into iterative programs.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Freytag, Johann Christoph; Goodman, Nathan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The problem of translating set-oriented query specifications intoiterative programs is explored and a translation using functionalprogramming and program transformation techniques is presented.andO;An algorithm is presented by which queries are translated into theiterative form.andP;  They are then simplified by sets oftransformation rules before the final iterative form is generated.andO;A second algorithm is presented which generates the iterative formmore quickly by means of a two-level translation withtransformation by a small set of rules taking place on the firstlevel and the functional combination on the second level producingthe final iterative form.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AlgorithmsData BasesProgramming LanguagesIterationRelational DBMS.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>